<div class="container">
  <div class="row justify-content-lg-center">
    <div class="col-lg-10">
      <h1>Submit <%= setting(:product) %> for review</h1>

      <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
        <center><strong>⚠️ ⚠️ ⚠️ Before you submit ⚠️ ⚠️ ⚠️ </strong></center>
        <p>As the submitting author, before you submit, please make sure that you have reviewed the following items. We promise this will make things go much more quickly during the technical screening process:
        <ul>
          <li>You have reviewed the <a href="https://docs.neurolibre.org/en/latest/PREPARE.html">submission instructions</a> and verified that your submission meets our <a href="https://joss.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submitting.html#submission-requirements">submission requirements</a>.</li>
          <li>The executable content of your reproducible preprint (e.g. MyST, Notebooks, Binder dependencies etc.) are organized by adhering to our <a href="https://docs.neurolibre.org/en/latest/SUBMISSION_STRUCTURE.html">repository structure.</a>.
          <li>The PDF summary <code>paper.md</code> is present in your repository and that is structured <a href="https://joss.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submitting.html#example-paper-and-bibliography">like this</a>, and you've tested it compiles properly using <a href='https://joss.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submitting.html#github-action'>this GitHub Action</a>.</li>
          <li>You have included the <a href="https://joss.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submitting.html#what-should-my-paper-contain">required sections</a> in your paper.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
      </div>

      <%= render partial: "form", locals: { paper: @paper } %>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
